cikePeerTable.name: cikePeerTable
cikePeerTable.description: The IPsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Peer Table. There is one entry in this table for each IPsec Phase-1 IKE peer association which is currently associated with an active IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel. The IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel associated with this IPsec Phase-1 IKE peer association may or may not be currently active.

cikePeerEntry.name: cikePeerEntry
cikePeerEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an IPsec Phase-1 IKE peer association.

cikePeerLocalType.name: cikePeerLocalType
cikePeerLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be identified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

cikePeerLocalValue.name: cikePeerLocalValue
cikePeerLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

cikePeerRemoteType.name: cikePeerRemoteType
cikePeerRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be identified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

cikePeerRemoteValue.name: cikePeerRemoteValue
cikePeerRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity. If the remote peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the remote peer.

cikePeerIntIndex.name: cikePeerIntIndex
cikePeerIntIndex.description: The internal index of the local-remote peer association. This internal index is used to uniquely identify multiple associations between the local and remote peer.

cikePeerLocalAddr.name: cikePeerLocalAddr
cikePeerLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local peer.

cikePeerRemoteAddr.name: cikePeerRemoteAddr
cikePeerRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote peer.

cikePeerActiveTime.name: cikePeerActiveTime
cikePeerActiveTime.description: The length of time that the peer association has existed in hundredths of a second.

cikePeerActiveTunnelIndex.name: cikePeerActiveTunnelIndex
cikePeerActiveTunnelIndex.description: The index of the active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (cikeTunIndex in the cikeTunnelTable) for this peer association. If an IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel is not currently active, then the value of this object will be zero.

cikeTunnelTable.name: cikeTunnelTable

cikeTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cikeTunIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

cikeTunLocalType.name: cikeTunLocalType
cikeTunLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be identified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

cikeTunLocalValue.name: cikeTunLocalValue
cikeTunLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

cikeTunOutNotifys.description: The total number of notifys sent by this IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel.

cipSecGlobalPreviousTunnels.description: The total number of previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalInOctets.name: cipSecGlobalInOctets
cipSecGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed. See also cipSecGlobalInOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalHcInOctets.name: cipSecGlobalHcInOctets
cipSecGlobalHcInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

cipSecGlobalInOctWraps.name: cipSecGlobalInOctWraps
cipSecGlobalInOctWraps.description: The number of times the global octets received counter (cipSecGlobalInOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalInDecompOctets.name: cipSecGlobalInDecompOctets
cipSecGlobalInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecGlobalInOctets. See also cipSecGlobalInDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalHcInDecompOctets.name: cipSecGlobalHcInDecompOctets

cipSecGlobalInDecompOctWraps.name: cipSecGlobalInDecompOctWraps
cipSecGlobalInDecompOctWraps.description: The number of times the global decompressed octets received counter (cipSecGlobalInDecompOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalInPkts.name: cipSecGlobalInPkts
cipSecGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalInDrops.name: cipSecGlobalInDrops
cipSecGlobalInDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

cipSecGlobalInReplayDrops.name: cipSecGlobalInReplayDrops

cipSecGlobalInAuths.name: cipSecGlobalInAuths
cipSecGlobalInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalInAuthFails.name: cipSecGlobalInAuthFails
cipSecGlobalInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalInDecryptFails.name: cipSecGlobalInDecryptFails

cipSecGlobalOutOctets.name: cipSecGlobalOutOctets

cipSecGlobalHcOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

cipSecGlobalOutOctWraps.name: cipSecGlobalOutOctWraps
cipSecGlobalOutOctWraps.description: The number of times the global octets sent counter (cipSecGlobalOutOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets.name: cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets
cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecGlobalOutOctets. See also cipSecGlobalOutDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalHcOutUncompOctets.name: cipSecGlobalHcOutUncompOctets

This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecGlobalHcOutOctets.

cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps.name: cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps
cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps.description: The number of times the global uncompressed octets sent counter (cipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecGlobalOutPkts.name: cipSecGlobalOutPkts
cipSecGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalOutDrops.name: cipSecGlobalOutDrops
cipSecGlobalOutDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecGlobalOutEncrypts.name: cipSecGlobalOutEncrypts
cipSecGlobalOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

cipSecTunOutSaCompAlgo.description: The compression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunInOctets.name: cipSecTunInOctets
cipSecTunInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed. See also cipSecTunInOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecTunHcInOctets.name: cipSecTunHcInOctets
cipSecTunHcInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

cipSecTunInOctWraps.name: cipSecTunInOctWraps
cipSecTunInOctWraps.description: The number of times the octets received counter (cipSecTunInOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecTunInDecompOctets.name: cipSecTunInDecompOctets
cipSecTunInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecTunInOctets. See also cipSecTunInDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecTunHcInDecompOctets.name: cipSecTunHcInDecompOctets
cipSecTunHcInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecTunHcInOctets.

cipSecTunInDecompOctWraps.name: cipSecTunInDecompOctWraps
cipSecTunInDecompOctWraps.description: The number of times the decompressed octets received counter (cipSecTunInDecompOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecTunInPkts.name: cipSecTunInPkts

cipSecTunInDecrypts.name: cipSecTunInDecrypts
cipSecTunInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunInDecryptFails.name: cipSecTunInDecryptFails
cipSecTunInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutOctets.name: cipSecTunOutOctets
cipSecTunOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed. See also cipSecTunOutOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

cipSecTunHcOutOctets.name: cipSecTunHcOutOctets
cipSecTunHcOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

cipSecTunOutOctWraps.name: cipSecTunOutOctWraps
cipSecTunOutOctWraps.description: The number of times the out octets counter (cipSecTunOutOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecTunOutUncompOctets.name: cipSecTunOutUncompOctets
cipSecTunOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. cipSecTunHcOutUncompOctets.name: cipSecTunHcOutUncompOctets
cipSecTunHcOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of cipSecTunHcOutOctets.

cipSecTunOutUncompOctWraps.name: cipSecTunOutUncompOctWraps
cipSecTunOutUncompOctWraps.description: The number of times the uncompressed octets sent counter (cipSecTunOutUncompOctets) has wrapped.

cipSecTunOutPkts.name: cipSecTunOutPkts
cipSecTunOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutDropPkts.name: cipSecTunOutDropPkts
cipSecTunOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutAuthFails.name: cipSecTunOutAuthFails
cipSecTunOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutEncrypts.name: cipSecTunOutEncrypts
cipSecTunOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecTunOutEncryptFails.name: cipSecTunOutEncryptFails

cipSecTunStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to bring the tunnel down by setting value of this object to destroy(2). When the value is set to destroy(2), the SA bundle is destroyed and this row is deleted from this table. When this MIB value is queried, the value of active(1) is always returned, if the instance exists. This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row.

cipSecEndPtTable.name: cipSecEndPtTable
cipSecEndPtTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Endpoint Table. This table contains an entry for each active endpoint associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cipSecEndPtEntry.name: cipSecEndPtEntry
cipSecEndPtEntry.description: An IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Endpoint entry.

cipSecEndPtIndex.name: cipSecEndPtIndex
cipSecEndPtIndex.description: The number of the Endpoint associated with the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each Endpoint associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

cipSecEndPtLocalName.name: cipSecEndPtLocalName
cipSecEndPtLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local Endpoint.

cipSecEndPtLocalType.name: cipSecEndPtLocalType
cipSecEndPtLocalType.description: The type of identity for the local Endpoint. Possible values are: 1) a single IP address, or 2) an IP address range, or 3) an IP subnet.

cipSecEndPtLocalAddr1.name: cipSecEndPtLocalAddr1
cipSecEndPtLocalAddr1.description: The local Endpoint's first IP address specification. If the local Endpoint type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the local Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet. If the local Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of beginning IP address of the range.

cipSecEndPtLocalAddr2.name: cipSecEndPtLocalAddr2
cipSecEndPtLocalAddr2.description: The local Endpoint's second IP address specification. If the local Endpoint type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the local Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet mask. If the local Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of ending IP address of the range.

cipSecEndPtLocalProtocol.name: cipSecEndPtLocalProtocol
cipSecEndPtLocalProtocol.description: The protocol number of the local Endpoint's traffic.

cipSecEndPtLocalPort.name: cipSecEndPtLocalPort
cipSecEndPtLocalPort.description: The port number of the local Endpoint's traffic.

cipSecEndPtRemoteName.name: cipSecEndPtRemoteName
cipSecEndPtRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote Endpoint.

cipSecEndPtRemoteType.name: cipSecEndPtRemoteType
cipSecEndPtRemoteType.description: The type of identity for the remote Endpoint. Possible values are: 1) a single IP address, or 2) an IP address range, or 3) an IP subnet.

cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr1.name: cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr1
cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr1.description: The remote Endpoint's first IP address specification. If the remote Endpoint type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the remote Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet. If the remote Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of beginning IP address of the range.

cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr2.name: cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr2
cipSecEndPtRemoteAddr2.description: The remote Endpoint's second IP address specification. If the remote Endpoint type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the remote Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet mask. If the remote Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of ending IP address of the range.

cipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol.name: cipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol
cipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol.description: The protocol number of the remote Endpoint's traffic.

cipSecEndPtRemotePort.name: cipSecEndPtRemotePort
cipSecEndPtRemotePort.description: The port number of the remote Endpoint's traffic.

cipSecSpiTable.name: cipSecSpiTable
cipSecSpiTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Security Protection Index Table. This table contains an entry for each active and expiring security association.

cipSecSpiEntry.name: cipSecSpiEntry
cipSecSpiEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with active and expiring IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

cipSecSpiIndex.name: cipSecSpiIndex
cipSecSpiIndex.description: The number of the SPI associated with the Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each SPI associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

cipSecHistTableSize.name: cipSecHistTableSize
cipSecHistTableSize.description: The window size of the IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables. The IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables are implemented as a sliding window in which only the last n entries are maintained. This object is used specify the number of entries which will be maintained in the IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables. An implementation may choose suitable minimum and maximum values for this element based on the local policy and available resources. If an SNMP SET request specifies a value outside this window for this element, a BAD VALUE may be returned.

cipSecHistCheckPoint.name: cipSecHistCheckPoint
cipSecHistCheckPoint.description: The current state of check point processing. This object will return ready when the agent is ready to create on-demand history entries for active IPsec Tunnels or checkPoint when the agent is currently creating on-demand history entries for active IPsec Tunnels. By setting this value to checkPoint, the agent will create: a) an entry in the IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel History for each active IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel and b) an entry in the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table and an entry in the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel EndPoint History Table for each active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

cikeTunnelHistTable.name: cikeTunnelHistTable
cikeTunnelHistTable.description: The IPsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Tunnel History Table. This table is implemented as a sliding window in which only the last n entries are maintained. The maximum number of entries is specified by the cipSecHistTableSize object.

cikeTunnelHistEntry.name: cikeTunnelHistEntry
cikeTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cikeTunHistIndex.name: cikeTunHistIndex
cikeTunHistIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel History Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

cikeTunHistTermReason.name: cikeTunHistTermReason
cikeTunHistTermReason.description: The reason the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel was terminated. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = normal termination 3 = operator request 4 = peer delete request was received 5 = contact with peer was lost 6 = local failure occurred. 7 = operator initiated check point request

cikeTunHistActiveIndex.name: cikeTunHistActiveIndex
cikeTunHistActiveIndex.description: The index of the previously active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cikeTunHistPeerLocalType.name: cikeTunHistPeerLocalType
cikeTunHistPeerLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

cikeTunHistPeerLocalValue.name: cikeTunHistPeerLocalValue
cikeTunHistPeerLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

cikeTunHistPeerIntIndex.name: cikeTunHistPeerIntIndex

cikeTunHistPeerRemoteType.name: cikeTunHistPeerRemoteType
cikeTunHistPeerRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

cikeTunHistPeerRemoteValue.name: cikeTunHistPeerRemoteValue

cikeTunHistRemoteAddr.name: cikeTunHistRemoteAddr
cikeTunHistRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cikeTunHistRemoteName.name: cikeTunHistRemoteName
cikeTunHistRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote IP address of IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the remote tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a NULL string.

cikeTunHistNegoMode.name: cikeTunHistNegoMode
cikeTunHistNegoMode.description: The negotiation mode of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp.name: cikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp
cikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cikeTunHistEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cikeTunHistHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cikeTunHistAuthMethod.name: cikeTunHistAuthMethod
cikeTunHistAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cikeTunHistLifeTime.name: cikeTunHistLifeTime
cikeTunHistLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel in seconds.

cikeTunHistStartTime.name: cikeTunHistStartTime
cikeTunHistStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds when the IPsec Phase-1 IKE tunnel was started.

cikeTunHistActiveTime.name: cikeTunHistActiveTime
cikeTunHistActiveTime.description: The length of time the IPsec Phase-1 IKE tunnel was been active in hundredths of seconds.

cikeTunHistTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security associations refreshes performed.
